ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: T: I can engage the student in a meaningful activity. / C: I can coach teachers to engage a child with ASD in a meaningful activity.
Notes: 1= Not at all confident; 2= A little confident; 3= Somewhat confident; 4=Very confident

ElementDescription: T: I can maintain the student's attention throughout a teaching sequence. / C: I can coach teachers to maintain the student's attention throughout a teaching sequence.
Notes: 1= Not at all confident; 2= A little confident; 3= Somewhat confident; 4=Very confident

ElementDescription: T: I can set up the environment or make an initial request in a way that the student understands the goal of the teaching sequence. / C: I can coach teachers to make a clear initial request or set up the environment in a way that the student understands the goal of the teaching sequence.
Notes: 1= Not at all confident; 2= A little confident; 3= Somewhat confident; 4=Very confident

ElementDescription: T: I can provide the student sufficient time (3-5 seconds) to perform the target skills after the initial request/ C: I can coach teachers to provide sufficient time (3-5 seconds) to perform the target skills after the initial request.
Notes: 1= Not at all confident; 2= A little confident; 3= Somewhat confident; 4=Very confident

ElementDescription: T: I can provide the student sufficient time (3-5 seconds) to perform the target skills following each prompt. / C: I can coach teachers to provide sufficient time (3-5 seconds) to perform the target skills following each prompt.
Notes: 1= Not at all confident; 2= A little confident; 3= Somewhat confident; 4=Very confident

ElementDescription: T: I can provide clear reinforcement for completing a skill. / C: I can coach teachers to provide clear reinforcement for completing a skill.
Notes: 1= Not at all confident; 2= A little confident; 3= Somewhat confident; 4=Very confident
